  "texts": [
    "To assess the normality of the data in this study, the Shapiro-Wilk and Kolmogorov-Smirnov statistical tests were employed.",
    "These tests are commonly used in statistical analysis to determine whether a sample follows a normal distribution.",
    "E. Statistical Analysis of the Scores of the Experimental and Control Group WorkShapiro-Wilk Test: This test was applied to smaller samples, as it is more suitable and has greater statistical power in such cases.",
    "The test compares the observed data with a theoretical normal distribution.",
    "If the data significantly deviate from normality, the resulting p-value will be less than 0.05, indicating that the data do not follow a normal distribution.Kolmogorov-Smirnov Test: This test was used as a backup to compare the empirical distribution of the data with a theoretical normal distribution."
